He's been granted a thousand rand bail the Blue Downs Magistrate's Court. He was arrested earlier and found in possession of firearms and explosive devices. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Another suspect linked to the Christian Resistance Movement has been arrested in Cape Town. A 46-year-old man from Kuilsrivier was found in possession of a firearm, explosives and explosive devices. READ: National Christian Resistance Movement leader arrested for alleged terrorism The man has appeared briefly at the Blue Downs Magistrate's Court and was granted R1,000 bail.
The Hawks made the arrest during an operation at his business premises. The suspect is believed to have links with others arrested and charged for alleged terrorist activities. READ: Suspects linked to terror plot to appear in court Johannes Knoesen who is believed to be the leader of the group was arrested last week.